14/09/2009
TIRANA, Albania -- French President Nicolas Sarkozy praised Albania's June 28th elections as a victory for democracy in the country, and its path towards European integration, local media reported on Sunday (September 13th).
In a letter to Prime Minister Sali Berisha, Sarkozy congratulated him on winning a second mandate and promised to help Tirana's efforts to win EU candidate status.
He encouraged Berisha to continue important reforms that have been undertaken.
(Balkan Web, Koha Jone, Top News, Telegrafi - 13/09/09)
